JOHANNESBURG – Supporters of former president Jacob Zuma gathered outside his home in Nkandla to show their support and solidarity. A handful of supporters were singing revolutionary songs outside the gate of his home, which controversially received a nearly R250-million facelift, with tax money. READ: Jacob Zuma, South Africa's president, in key dates eNCA's Siphamandla Goge caught up with residents in the area to hear their thoughts on the resignation tendered by Zuma on Wednesday night. Some supporters still had questions over the resignation, wanting to know reasons behind his recall. “Usulile noma inina enimsulile,” one person said, which loosely translated means: "Did he resign or you are the ones who fired him?" ANC KwaNxamalala ward 14 councillor Bongokwakhe Mbambo believes Zuma will help the ANC wrestle control of the local municipality from the Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP). eNCA